px-proxy (0.4.0.linux.6) unofficial; urgency=low

  * px: pass --config argument through tilde expansion for consistency
  * px: use FHS-compliant location of conffile on Linux
    (~/.config/px-proxy/px-proxy.ini instead of ~/px.ini)
  * px: create missing dirs when writing out ini file
  * px: facilitate renaming of ini file in code-base
  * px.desktop: integrate with desktop environments

 -- Daniel Kobras (Puzzle ITC) <kobras@puzzle-itc.de>  Mon, 09 Dec 2019 17:33:05 +0100

px-proxy (0.4.0.linux.5) unofficial; urgency=low

  * px: central config for prog and srv names
  * px: handle arg groups in Gooey compat wrapper
  * px: add proper GUI widget to password option
  * px: catch gssapi errors when running w/o krb creds
  * debian: rename package, executable, and systemd service to px-proxy to
    avoid clash with official Debian packages of https://github.com/walles/px/
  * debian: recommend Gooey for GUI support

